Hey, man.

43
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:27,516
I know you think you're excited
about Miami...

44
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:31,070
...but I cannot wait for you
to meet the guys at Nana's condo.

45
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:34,073
We got Abe, we got Stu,
we got Stanley.

46
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,476
Although I think Stanley
may have passed on.

47
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,278
He had a prostate thing. I hope not.

48
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:40,271
-I can't go.
-What? Why not?

49
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,919
Everything with me and Marissa.

50
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:44,355
-ls awesome.
-Fine, okay. But there's Trey.

51
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:48,479
Who's also doing awesome.
Ryan, face it, you got no excuses.

52
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,631
Everything's great.
You deserve a vacation.

53
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:53,030
We, actually, deserve a vacation, Ryan.

54
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,792
And it would mean a lot to my dad.

55
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,468
-Yeah. He is kind of worked up.
-He's gonna need company.

56
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,198
-Well, he's got you.
-I can't, man.

57
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,588
My schedule's all booked up.

58
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,716
I got pinochle with the ladies
on Saturday.

59
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:04,313
Bridge Sunday with the fellas.

60
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:07,558
Gotta see if I can get on that
bingo cruise. That'll be awesome.

61
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:10,234
-What about you and Summer?
-I'm gonna go apologize...

62
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:12,311
...extremely sincerely...

63
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:15,552
...and then I'm gonna get out of town
before I do anything else wrong.

64
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:18,598
What do you say? Miami. Miami.

65
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:21,069
Miami? Miami. Miami.

66
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:23,470
Miami. Miami.

67
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,952
-Miami.
-Miami.

68
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,715
Honey, do you have
my American Advantage number?

69
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:33,553
I'm on AA.com and I'm trying
to use my miles to upgrade.

70
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,870
You know me, l--
I hate sitting in the middle.

71
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:37,268
It's in my purse.

72
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:40,398
But what's the rush? It's not like
she's getting married tomorrow.

73
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:43,233
Well, I know. It's just....
I love my mother.

74
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,391
-But who else would?
-That's terrible.

75
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,357
You wouldn't say the same
about your dad?

76
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:50,273
-You make a good point.
-She was so happy on the phone...

77
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:53,352
...I just wanna make sure
everything works out of her. Great.

78
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:56,159
You know, especially after
the year she's had.

79
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:58,595
You are a good son.

80
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:01,513
Oh, yeah? How about husband?

81
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,597
Definitely top five.

82
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:08,033
Miami, huh?
Well, have a hell of a time then.

83
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:12,193
-Thanks. You'll be all right?
-Don't worry, Mom. I'll be fine.

84
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,359
Yo, Ry, look, I gotta jump.

85
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:19,717
I-- Probably the landlord
complaining about something.

86
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,438
Yeah.

87
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,794
Well, have fun.

88
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,234
See you.

89
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:29,868
Definitely not the landlord.

90
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,959
Hey, you.

91
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,993
So...

92
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,630
...I just wanted to come by
to say thanks again.

93
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,791
For not selling me out.

94
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,592
Have you met Don Julio?

95
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:46,311
Yeah. Me and the Don go way back.

96
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,115
-Thanks for the gift.
-Oh, that's not the gift.

97
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:53,235
I figure a guy's been in prison
for 1 8 months...

98
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,994
...probably got pretty lonely.

99
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:01,794
You have no idea.

100
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,556
Hey, Summer. Busy?

101
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:15,792
-What do you want, Cohen?
-To talk.

102
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,034
Yeah?

103
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:21,078
-Hold my bag.
-Anything for my million-dollar baby.

104
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:25,318
-So look, I just came to apologize.
-Why?

105
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:29,155
Because I was humiliated in front of
all your oh-so-hip, super dorked out...

106
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:31,959
...indie-music-loving comic-book geeks,
who looked at me...

107
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:34,111
...Iike I was some dimwit
Orange County ho?

108
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,879
Yeah. But that was never
my intention, okay?

109
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:41,157
I really only wanted you there
to be a part of everything with me.

110
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:44,756
There's no point in you apologizing.
You can no longer make me upset.

111
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:47,718
-You're just immune to my charms?
-Working on it.

112
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,677
But you know what I could use?

113
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,159
A timeout.

114
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:56,828
Okay. Well, you know....
Good.

115
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:59,197
Actually, that's good timing because...

116
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:02,079
...I'm headed to Miami to see
the nana, so....

117
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,868
Well, perfect.
Go to Miami, get wasted...

118
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,600
...and wind up on Music Video Nation's
Spring Break special.

119
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:10,672
It's not like that. The only thing
I'll be drinking is Metamucil.

120
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:12,831
Oh, yeah, like I'm gonna believe that.

121
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,956
Look, just go. Go sow your oats.

122
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:18,476
Get all of your Cohen-y, Cohen-ish
Cohen-isms out of your system.

123
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,868
And when I get back?

124
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:21,954
We'll see.

125
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,159
Hi.

126
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,353
Hey.

127
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,792
So just imagine...

128
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:41,476
...a whole weekend of nothing but this.

129
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:44,270
If you could hold that thought
till next weekend.

130
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:45,998
Why? You going somewhere?

131
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,754
Yeah, actually. Miami.

132
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,950
South Beach
for a little spring-break action?

133
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,712
-Meet come college girls?
-Not quite.

134
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:57,155
Going with Seth and Sandy
to see the nana.

135
00:06:57,320 --> 00:07:00,278
-That's really sweet. That'll be fun.
-Yeah. No, it will be.

136
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:03,796
It's just, I don't know, I kind of feel
weird leaving Trey here by himself.

137
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:05,154
I can hang out with him.

138
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:08,995
Yeah, really? Because I was kind of
gonna help him find a job.

139
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:12,753
-I got it covered.
-Thanks, I owe you.

140
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,639
Yes, you do.

141
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:20,079
You do owe me. A whole weekend
of nothing but this.

142
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,551
That I can do.

143
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:29,918
All right, you got all the numbers?
My cell phone, Fontainebleau...

144
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,593
-...the nana?
-I got the numbers.

145
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:35,070
And you remember how to set
the alarm to "no delay. "

146
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:38,312
-lf the alarm goes off, the code is...?
-"Greased lightning. "

147
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,994
-Yes. Do you need any cash?
-I have plenty of money.

148
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:43,151
-I gassed up your car.
-Which I so appreciate.

149
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,675
-Are you gonna be fine?
-I'll be fine.

150
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,398
I love you.

151
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:51,557
-The question is, are you gonna be okay?
-Oh, yeah.

152
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,918
Fellas, you got everything?

153
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:58,913
I got my cardigan,
my orthopedic shoes and my humidifier.

154
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:00,274
Now take me to my people.

155
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,433
-Bye.
-Bye.

156
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,556
-Bye.
-Bye-bye.

157
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:36,993
Is Carter in the office?

158
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:51,314
In the immortal words of Will Smith:

159
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,313
"Welcome to Miami. "

160
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:56,597
There's too many young, tan,
healthy people here. I don't like it.

161
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,079
Well, let's check in anyway.

162
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,593
-Who wants some dinner?
-Yeah.

163
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,352
It's 4 p.m. in Orange County.

164
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:03,715
They put us on the early-bird circuit.

165
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,913
-Hey.
-Hey.

166
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:10,230
I have the weekend to myself.

167
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,914
I thought we could roll up our sleeves,
really dig in...

168
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,877
...and maybe even get
a few issues ahead.

169
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,873
Well, I'd hold on to that thought
if I were you.

170
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:21,635
Turns out Newport Living, which l
thought was the last nail in the coffin...

171
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:25,475
...that is my career,
is actually the thing that saved it.

172
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,997
You got another job offer.

173
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,633
Well, Carter, that's great.

174
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,028
Thanks.

175
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:37,037
Yeah, so l-- I fly out on Monday.

176
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,239
Fly out where?

177
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:42,631
New York. That's where the job is,
and they're relocating me.

178
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:46,313
-You're leaving.
-I am.

179
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:50,910
But my publisher is lining up someone
to replace me.

180
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:54,755
You know, someone who is smarter
and better at this than I am.

181
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:56,319
So...

182
00:09:57,720 --> 00:10:00,678
...I hope you don't think
I'm jumping ship.

183
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,588
Because you are.

184
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:08,598
It's really great.

185
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:22,390
I was thinking we could have
a farewell dinner.

186
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,192
-You know what? We should.
-Great.

187
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,112
I'll make a reservation at Arches.

188
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:29,317
Or you could come by the house
tomorrow.

189
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,072
I'll cook.

190
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,992
Man. I thought Newport was nice.

191
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:39,479
-This is something, huh?
-Yeah.

192
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:43,553
If you're a fan of the vibrant nightlife.
Why can't we go see the nana tonight?

193
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:45,278
You know the nana and her schedule.

194
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,759
-Friday night's mahjong.
-What?

195
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:48,797
-Yeah.
-Since when is Friday night mahjong?

196
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:51,872
-That totally throws off my schedule.
-Breathe it in, boys.

197
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:54,918
We got a weekend away
with nothing to worry about.

198
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,556
Oh, hey. Sorry.

199
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,278
Marissa. What's up?

200
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,873
Ryan took off for Miami, huh?

201
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:11,874
Y eah. So I just wanted you to know
that while he's gone, I'm here.

202
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,633
Cool.

203
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:17,551
You know, you don't have to
if you don't want.

204
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,153
No, I want to.

205
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:22,153
And, you know, I thought maybe
tomorrow we could go job-hunting.

206
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:24,431
That sounds great.

207
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:27,428
I thought with Ryan gone
I was gonna be alone in Newport.

208
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:30,273
No, not on my watch.
So I'll see you tomorrow.

209
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,032
-Can't wait.
-Okay.

210
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,958
You and Marissa Cooper?

211
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,838
Yeah, right.

212
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:57,920
-It's not like that.
-lt sure isn't.

213
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,957
Not in this lifetime.

214
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,678
Or in this town.

215
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,519
Your move.

216
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,591
-You're playing with him?
-Yeah.

217
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,796
-I thought you were playing with me.
-With him.

218
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,552
No, l-- I just moved.

219
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,472
-Now we're talking.
-I'm with him.

220
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:34,950
-All right, so I'll watch.
-Abe, Stu, Stanley.

221
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,951
-Hey, look who's here.
-How are you?

222
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:39,236
-Terrible.
-Worse, worse.

223
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,799
How's your nervous stomach?

224
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:43,997
-You still got shpilkes?
-Why don't you have a seat.

225
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:48,559
-You need my heating pad?
-Back's a little sore. Back's a little sore.

226
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:51,234
All right. Now I'm officially terrified.

227
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,311
He doesn't have
this many friends at school.

228
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:56,313
So they do fly airplanes
from Orange County to Miami.

229
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:58,311
I wouldn't know. I see so little of you.

230
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,118
Ma.

231
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:04,638
-You look better than ever.
-Yeah? I'm getting married.

232
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,919
-You remember Ryan.
-Of course.

233
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:09,594
Who would forget with those arms?

234
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,037
You know, if I weren't engaged....

235
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,837
There's my grandson.

236
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,878
-Hello, bubeleh.
-Hello, Nana.

237
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:24,195
I want you to tell me everything that's
gone on for you this whole last year.

238
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:28,792
I can barely remember
what I had for dinner last night. Please.

239
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,393
-Welcome to the club.
-Me too.

240
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,391
You know.

