00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:35,509
-You wanna talk?
-Sure I do.

242
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:39,195
You keep an eye on him, make sure
he doesn't die of old age, huh?

243
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:44,993
Is this Metamucil malted?

244
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:50,676
-Kirsten couldn't make it?
-Well, she wanted to.

245
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,594
So how are things with you two?

246
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:57,593
To be honest, they've been better.

247
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,390
You two will work it out.

248
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:05,917
Since when did you become
such a romantic?

249
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,911
Falling in love will do that to you.

250
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:11,072
Speaking of which,
I have photos from the place...

251
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:14,755
...where we're holding
the ceremony in June.

252
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,990
So you should book your tickets now.

253
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,878
Whoa, June. What's the rush?

254
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:21,110
-You pregnant?
-Yeah, yeah. Very funny.

255
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:25,193
Listen, you go through a year like I did,
you don't wanna waste any time.

256
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:28,670
Besides, I wanna move
before the summer storms hit.

257
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:31,991
-You're moving?
-Yeah. Bobby is 1 2 years my junior.

258
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,991
This place skews a little old for him.

259
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,754
We're gonna move to the condo
you bought me in Sarasota.

260
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:39,832
-lt was meant to be lived in.
-Bobby flipped when he saw it.

261
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,037
Beachfront, unbeatable location.
Why wouldn't he?

262
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,189
I know what you're thinking, Sanford.

263
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:48,555
And cynicism is a Cohen family trait.

264
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:51,792
-Yeah, well, I learned from the master.
-Yeah, well....

265
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:54,155
Nonetheless, he's a good guy.

266
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:55,992
And he can move his practice anywhere.

267
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:58,993
Everybody always needs
a good chiropractor.

268
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,471
Not another word.

269
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:06,870
-I can't wait to meet him.
-Very good.

270
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:09,270
-Eat your lunch.
-Yes, Ma.

271
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,559
Summer.

272
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:18,756
Hey, Summer.

273
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,794
Oh, God.

274
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:25,838
Zach, I'm so sorry. Are you okay?
I was in a rage blackout.

275
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,150
My therapist said boxing
might help me through it.

276
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:30,754
I came to see if you were okay
after the other night.

277
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:33,229
I'm in gym clothes,
and my hair is in French braids.

278
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,719
So I'm terrible.

279
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:37,348
Cohen and I are on a timeout.

280
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:42,070
He went to Miami to party it up
like he always does this time of year...

281
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:45,471
-...when we're on a timeout.
-Are you too full of rage to hang out?

282
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:48,154
-Maybe come over for dinner?
-No offense, but hanging...

283
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:51,869
-...with your family sounds bad.
-Oh, no, I totally understand.

284
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:55,558
They're in Aspen
for an economics conference.

285
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:59,512
Come on. I'll cook. Italian.

286
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,796
Francesca gave me a great recipe.

287
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:06,954
Choke.

288
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,519
Sit down.

289
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:11,874
Sorry, figure of speech. Victory lap.

290
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,558
My people.

291
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:20,549
-You cleaned his clock.
-Not that he'll pay up. Cheap bastard.

292
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,671
Hey, Seth, what do you say?

293
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:26,435
-You ready to roll? I'm really hungry.
-Hey, I'm famished too.

294
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,909
It doesn't seem like
there's anybody left to beat...

295
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:32,516
...so why don't we go into the dining
hall. We're gonna have lunch. My treat.

296
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:37,113
-I can't beat that. That's great.
-Can I get in on the action?

297
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:41,758
Mary Sue. Nice to meet you.

298
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:43,672
This is my grandma, Mary Ellen.

299
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,639
Hello.

300
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,995
Actually, we were gonna go eat.

301
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,230
-Right?
-Yeah. Well, you like food?

302
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:52,518
One round?

303
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,713
Sure.

304
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,472
Sure. This will just take a second.

305
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:58,437
Okay. Rack them, sir.

306
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:11,671
-Hey, how'd it go?
-My dream's come true.

307
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:13,637
-I'm cleaning toilets.
-You got it?

308
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:16,234
-I start tomorrow.
-Oh, that's great.

309
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:22,599
So we....
We gotta celebrate tonight, okay?

310
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:25,991
-I will make margaritas.
-I'll bring the guacamole.

311
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,913
It sounds like a party.

312
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:31,269
But I gotta stay here,
fill out some paperwork...

313
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:33,633
...so I'll see you tonight.

314
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,677
-Okay.
-And hey, thanks.

315
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:40,073
-I feel like my life's coming together.
-Hey, I'm happy to help.

316
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,912
So I'll see you later.

317
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:59,992
I do believe we have
a new shuffleboard champion.

318
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,312
-I can't believe she beat me.
-I can.

319
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:07,153
-Can we eat now?
-No. I won't go down like that.

320
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:10,073
These people look up to me.
I'm like a god to them.

321
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:12,231
You wanna lose again?

322
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:15,517
I wanna play again. Only this time,
why don't we make it interesting?

323
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:18,797
A little wager. You wanna do money?
You wanna do food?

324
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:21,758
You want me to streak naked
through the bingo hall?

325
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:23,558
Actually...

326
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:28,593
-...I do need a partner.
-Partner?

327
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,558
-What kind of partner?
-Well...

328
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:35,350
...besides being down here to visit my
grandma, I entered into a dance contest.

329
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,790
-A dance contest?
-For Music Video Nation.

330
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:42,191
For their big Spring Break special.

331
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:47,070
And the winner gets $5000, which
would really help with my college loans.

332
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:51,719
That sounds very reasonable, Mary Sue.

333
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:56,716
Only move she's getting out of me
is a victory dance.

334
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:01,555
What up, what up, what up?

335
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:04,029
Yeah. My name's Swerve.

336
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:08,474
The host of MVN's Sp-- Sp--
Spring Break.

337
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:12,953
Coming at you live from South Beach.

338
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:17,678
Hi, I'm Pixie, one of the star's
of Sherman Oaks: The Real Valley.

339
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,911
All right. I hope you' re all crunked up...

340
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:24,719
... because this next performance's
gonna be off the chain...

341
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:27,269
...and totally
bananas-oh-bananas-oh-bananas.

342
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:30,955
Bring them out from my dogs
from the dirty South:

343
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:32,473
T.I.!

344
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:04,879
Who knew, man? I've never played
anyone under 85 before.

345
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:07,474
-Right.
-The registration tent is over there.

346
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,232
-We need to sign in.
-Okay. So...

347
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:13,234
...what kind of dancing are we talking?
A little jazz step, a little soft-shoe?

348
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,675
-Actually, it's not quite a dance contest.
-lt isn't?

349
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:17,034
No.

350
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:21,757
-She's got whipped cream, Seth.
-I know. Maybe she's baking a cake.

351
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:25,117
I'm gonna cover myself in whipped
cream, and you're gonna lick it off...

352
00:20:25,280 --> 00:20:28,795
...and eat a cherry out of my mouth
before any of the other contestants.

353
00:20:29,040 --> 00:20:30,234
Did she say "cherry"?

354
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:32,675
If we win, it would mean so much
to my grandma.

355
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:34,876
Not having to worry about
my college loans.

356
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:37,431
With all the money she spends
on medication.

357
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:39,393
Yeah.

358
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:42,439
It's her grandma.

359
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,874
What does she have?

360
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:47,032
Yeah, well, just hope Summer
hasn't paid her cable bill.

361
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:05,390
-Ryan.
-Hello?

362
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,357
Hey, what's going on?

363
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:11,070
It's actually kind of a long story.
Can you do me a favor?

364
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:14,676
If you see Summer, could you please
keep her away from the television?

365
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:18,116
Well, actually, I was going
over to Trey's to celebrate.

366
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:20,157
-He got a job.
-Really?

367
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:21,719
That's awesome.

368
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:24,952
They disqualified me
from the wet T-shirt contest.

369
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,350
But don't they look real?

370
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:31,278
Wait. That wasn't the nana, was it?

371
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:33,556
Oh, my God. I'm gonna puke.

372
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:37,597
Actually, I'm...

373
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:39,473
...kind of wishing I was home now.

374
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:42,474
Yeah, I'm kind of wishing that too.

375
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:48,430
-Stay out of trouble, okay?
-All right. Back at you.

376
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:56,193
-It's like an Olive Garden around here.
-Buongiorno, Summer.

377
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:59,830
So, what is gnocchi?

378
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,355
I don't know. I'm making gnocchi.

379
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:04,593
You've never had gnocchi before.

380
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:08,116
No, I've never heard of it until
five seconds ago. How do you say it?

381
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:09,713
Gnocchi.

382
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,313
Gnocchi.

383
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:17,388
Listen, I'm gonna be a while,
so I'm gonna turn on the TV here.

384
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:20,757
MVN's Spring Break special.

385
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:26,040
I took the ltalian thing
a little too far there, didn't l?

386
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,918
You had me at buongiorno.

387
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:29,914
Thanks for having me over.

388
00:22:30,280 --> 00:22:32,111
And don't worry,
I won't talk about Cohen.

389
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:35,317
Oh, Cohen or no Cohen,
I'm just here for the gnocchi.

390
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:43,068
-I really want you to like him, Sandy.
-Oh, me too, Ma.

391
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:44,719
-Me too.
-There he is.

392
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:48,832
-Hey. Sandy Cohen. Pleasure.
-Bobby Mills.

393
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,958
Heard a lot about you. Hey, sweetie.

394
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,874
It's unbelievable.

395
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:56,679
You look way too young
to have a son this old.

396
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:59,308
-Hey, no offense.
-Why would I be offended?

397
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:05,188
I have to tinkle, so....
You two have a lot to talk about.

398
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:06,998
Mainly me.

399
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:13,830
She's a great lady, huh? Your mom.
What a pistol.

400
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,070
I always thought of her
as more of an AK-47.

401
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:20,670
I gotta tell you, since she's met you,
she has mellowed. My mother in love.

402
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:23,559
-I never thought I'd see the day.
-She came into my clinic...

403
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:26,712
...I cracked her back,
and the rest is history.

404
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,589
That is so romantic.

405
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:31,480
I'm just so happy she's met
a nice guy, you know.

406
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:33,229
An honest guy.

407
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:36,116
-Well, thank you, Sandy.
-Oh, thank you.

408
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:39,829
Listen, there are a lot of guys, they see
an older woman not in perfect health...

409
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,560
...with a million-dollar condo
in her name....

410
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,752
We've all seen 60 Minutes, haven't we?

411
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:48,276
Well, I'm more a Dateline guy.
I like that Stone Phillips.

412
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:49,793
Who doesn't?

413
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:53,799
You know, I was a public defender
for many years...

414
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:55,678
...and my tendency is to be suspicious.

415
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:59,071
It's a problem for me, Bobby.
You know, I've got trust issues.

416
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:02,357
I'm working on it. I'm working on it.

417
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:04,074
But I got a ways to go.

418
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:07,160
-You can trust me, Sandy.
-Well, that's what I figured.

419
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:09,754
You know, I tell my cop friends,
my buddies at the FBl.

420
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,593
They say, "Sandy, let me run
a background check on this guy. "

421
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:15,957
You know what I say? I said, "No. "

422
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:20,799
Sophie Cohen is still pretty sharp.
If she trusts you...

423
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:22,998
...I trust you.

424
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:30,358
Great news. They have fresh crab.

425
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:33,193
Oh, it can't be better than Joe's.

426
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:36,158
Bobby, you like Joe's stone crab?

427
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:38,834
Yeah. I love them.

428
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:44,113
I figured you've been out of the loop.
You need to catch up on your movies.

429
00:24:44,280 --> 00:24:46,430
Margaritas and movies. Sure.

430
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:48,113
What do you got?

431
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:51,428
The best movie of, like, all time.

432
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,033
The Notebook.

433
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:57,114
I'm kind of more of a shoot-'em-up
type guy, where people, like, die.

434
00:24:57,760 --> 00:24:59,910
Well, James Garner doesn't fair so well.

435
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:02,435
Great. If it's your favorite movie...

436
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:03,794
...I'm in.

437
00:25:04,120 --> 00:25:05,838
A toast to you.

438
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:08,714
-Thank you.
-Oh, to me? I like that toast.

439
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:39,870
Hey. I'm a little early.

440
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:42,031
It's okay. I-- I just finished.

441
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:44,238
You made all this?

442
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:46,675
It's amazing what I can do
when I'm off work.

443
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:49,074
Who knew?

444
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:53,879
Would you like some wine?

445
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:03,152
Hi.

446
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:05,595
I've been doing, like,
a little bit of thinking...

447
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:07,990
...and I'm not so sure
I'm the guy for this job.

448
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:10,196
-You're backing out on me?
-No, no.

449
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,032
It's not that. It's just, you know...

450
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:15,476
...there's whipped cream,
and I'm a little lactose intolerant, so....

451
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:18,029
If you back out on me,
I have no chance to win.

452
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,430
And Grandma Mary Ellen
won't pay her medical bills.

453
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:22,909
And I'll have to drop out of college.

454
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:28,073
Well, I'm a fan of Medicaid
and education...

455
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:29,719
...so okay.

456
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:32,792
-Thank you. Thank you so much.
-Sure.

457
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:36,554
-It's almost time to get ready.
-Okay.

458
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,472
What do we do?

459
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:52,119
Hey, man. Can I get
a bottle of water, please?

460
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:53,508
How you doing?

461
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:55,955
-I'm all right. You?
-Bad.

462
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:57,838
-I can't find my girlfriend.
-Oh, yeah?

463
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:59,956
-Lost her in the crowd?
-I lost her last night.

464
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:02,395
Told me she was coming to Florida
to see her grandma.

465
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:05,552
But her best friend told me
she entered some contest down here.

466
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:07,597
Immodestly revealing her body
for money.

467
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:10,029
Yeah, well, spring break.

468
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:13,112
-That does happen.
-Doesn't happen where we're from.

469
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:15,350
-Where's that?
-Bob Jones University.

470
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:18,080
They find out what she's doing here,
she'll be expelled.

471
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:20,708
Which won't matter
when she's burning in hell.

472
00:27:21,400 --> 00:27:23,197
-Yeah, that's rough.
-The worst part is...

473
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:26,352
...I think she's cheating on me
with whoever her partner in sin is.

474
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:28,750
That's why I brought my boys with me.

475
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:31,195
-Oh, yeah? Your frat brothers?
-Bible-study buddies.

476
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:34,955
We get a hold of who's corrupting her,
it's gonna be Judgment Day for him.

477
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:36,633
And Mary Sue.

